Running back Tru Wilson, a favorite of Michigan fans for his tough blocking and hard running, has transferred to Northern Colorado.
Running back Tru Wilson will play at Northern Colorado as a graduate transfer.
He played in 26 games during his Michigan career, including 21 at running back.
In early January, Wilson announced his plans to move on as a graduate transfer.
Michigan fans appreciating Wilson’s tough running would chant “Truuuuu” when he had the ball.